article.description: Quin Humphrey scored 25 points to lead Youngstown State to a 74-50 win over Central Michigan in the first round of the 2K College Hoops Classic.
article.headline: Humphrey lifts Youngstown State past Central Michigan
article.linkText: Humphrey lifts Youngstown State past Central Michigan
article.story: EAST LANSING, Mich. (AP) -- Quin Humphrey scored 25 points to lead Youngstown State to a 74-50 win over Central Michigan on Wednesday in the first round of the 2K College Hoops Classic. The Penguins had a 44-18 advantage late in the first half. Humphrey had 19 points before the break as Youngstown State (1-0) shot 52 percent in the first 20 minutes and held the Chippewas (0-1) to 20 percent from the floor. John Barber added 13 points for the Penguins, who protected their lead by hitting 26 free throws. Sefton Barrett came off the bench to lead Central Michigan with 12 points and eight rebounds. None of Barrett's teammates had more than eight points in Ernie Zeigler's first game as head coach of the Chippewas. Youngstown State will face Michigan State on Thursday night in the regional championship of the 16-team event, while Central Michigan will face Brown in a consolation game. Michigan State beat Brown 45-34 on Wednesday night.
